  "notes": "Gun / Gungbe (Gbe, Benin), written in the Benin national alphabet (Africa-alphabet based; closely following Fon). Special letters: ⟨ɛ⟩ /ɛ/, ⟨ɔ⟩ /ɔ/, ⟨ɖ⟩ /ɖ/; digraphs ⟨gb⟩ /ɡ͡b/, ⟨kp⟩ /k͡p/, ⟨xw⟩ /xʷ/, ⟨hw⟩ /hʷ/, ⟨ny⟩ /ɲ/. A vowel followed by ⟨n⟩ (an, ɛn, in, ɔn, un) writes a nasal vowel. /b ɖ l/ surface as [m n n] before nasal vowels. Gungbe is tonal (H/L); tone is not consistently written and is therefore not recoverable from ordinary spelling."
